End-user segmentation highlights hospitals as the major consumers of ureteroscopy devices, owing to the high patient inflow and availability of advanced medical facilities. However, ambulatory surgical centers are emerging as a rapidly growing segment due to their cost-effective nature and convenience for patients seeking outpatient procedures. Specialty clinics also play a significant role in the market, catering to specific urological needs and procedures.

The indication for which ureteroscopy is performed is another crucial segmentation factor in this market. Common indications such as kidney stones, ureteral strictures, and urothelial carcinoma are driving the demand for ureteroscopy procedures globally. With the increasing prevalence of kidney stones around the world, the market for ureteroscopy devices is expected to experience sustained growth over the forecast period.

